com.ihealth.communication.control

Class Bg5Control

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ihealth.communication.control.Bg5Control
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DeviceControl, IBGDelegate

    public class Bg5Control
extends java.lang.Object
implements IBGDelegate
    Public API for the BG5

    The class provides methods to control BG5 device. You need to call the device method, and then call the connection method

    If you want to connect a BG5 device, you need to calliHealthDevicesManager.startDiscovery(long) to discovery a new BG5 device, and then calliHealthDevicesManager.connectDevice(java.lang.String, java.lang.String, java.lang.String)to connect BG5 device.

    • Method Detail

      • setTime

        public void setTime()
        Set time to Bg5 device.
        • Attention, call iHealthDevicesManager.registerClientCallback(iHealthDevicesCallback) firstly.
        • This is an asynchronous call, it will not return immediately. After set time successfully, Callback iHealthDevicesCallback.onDeviceNotify(String, String, String, String) will be triggered.
        • The action of the callback is Bg5Profile.ACTION_SET_TIME, the keys of message will show in the KeyList of action.
        Specified by:
        setTime in interface IBGDelegate
